				<p>
					Next, we must compute the derivative <m>f'</m> to the left and right of each of the points above.  
					There are three intervals: to the left of 0, between 0 and 8, and to the right of 8.  
					You can chose any number in those intervals.
					<dl>
						<li>
							<title>left of 0</title>
							<m>f'(-5) = (-5)^3 - 8(-5)^2 = \dots = (-)</m>
						</li>
						<li>
							<title>between 0 and 8</title>
							<m>f'(1) = (1)^3 - 8(-1)^2 = \dots = (-)</m>
						</li>
						<li>
							<title>right of 8</title>
							<m>f'(10) = (10)^3 - 8(10)^2 = \dots = (+)</m>
						</li>
					</dl>
					Mark the magnitude of the derivative below the interval, and draw an <m>\nearrow</m> or <m>\searrow</m> above the line to indicate the behavior of the function.
				</p>
				<p>
					<image width="50%" xml:id="image_maxminexample2_signchartv2">
						<latex-image>
							\begin{tikzpicture}
								\draw[latex-latex, very thick] (-2,0) -- (12,0);
								\def\xval{0 } \draw[fill] (\xval,0) circle (2pt) node [below] {$\xval$};
								\def\xval{8 } \draw[fill] (\xval,0) circle (2pt) node [below] {$\xval$};


								\def\xval{-1} \draw[stealth-,double,red] (\xval,-0.25) -- (\xval,-0.75) node[below] {\scriptsize $f'(\xval)=(-)$};
														\node[red] at (\xval,0.4) {\large $\searrow$};
								\def\xval{1} \draw[stealth-,double,red] (\xval,-0.25) -- (\xval,-0.75) node[below] {\scriptsize $f'(\xval)=(-)$};
														\node[red] at (\xval,0.4) {\large $\searrow$};
								\def\xval{10} \draw[stealth-,double,red] (\xval,-0.25) -- (\xval,-0.75) node[below] {\scriptsize $f'(\xval)=(+)$};
